<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Ramatseba told Daily Sun: “This was the biggest dagga bust in our province. The truck was stopped along the N1 about 10km outside Colesberg to Hanover at about 6pm. “The compressed dagga, weighing about 244kg, was recovered from a truck and has an estimated street value of R36 million.” He said the truck, which was accompanied by a car, had been on the way from Mpumalanga to Cape Town in Western Cape.“Three men aged 34, 36 and 50 were arrested on the spot. “The truck as well as the car used were impounded for further investigation.”He said the suspects were charged with dealing in dagga and were due to appear in the Colesberg Magistrates Court today.